<div id="review_2927658576" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2927658576" />
    <a title="Gabi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/84001290-gabi"><img alt="Gabi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1608919962p2/84001290.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2927658576?book_show_action=true">Aug 10, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gabi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gabi" href="/user/show/84001290-gabi">Gabi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/84001290-gabi?shelf=locus_nominees">locus_nominees</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/84001290-gabi?shelf=hugo_winners">hugo_winners</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2927658576" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15351759480980840239">3.5 stars, rounded up, cause I guess some of my problems with this book was the not-so-fortunate presentation of the audiobook. The narrator read women and Hisa with childlike voices which made me grind my teeth. <br/><br/>From &quot;Cyteen&quot; I already was prepared for the dry prose and the drawn out talky parts, so after not being able to connect with the characters I just let it flow. Other than Cyteen it took me nearly half of the book to get into the story. It felt a lot like a lecture on social, economic a</span>
  <span id="freeText15351759480980840239" style="display:none">3.5 stars, rounded up, cause I guess some of my problems with this book was the not-so-fortunate presentation of the audiobook. The narrator read women and Hisa with childlike voices which made me grind my teeth. <br /><br />From "Cyteen" I already was prepared for the dry prose and the drawn out talky parts, so after not being able to connect with the characters I just let it flow. Other than Cyteen it took me nearly half of the book to get into the story. It felt a lot like a lecture on social, economic and military dynamics. Very well done, but completely lacking emotional depth. The parts with the Hisa, the endemic species of Pell, turned out the most interesting ones for me.<br /><br />The last third finally got me hooked, which is the reason why it didn't end with 3 stars. I guess less pages would have been more in this case.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15351759480980840239" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
