        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780756405502" href="/book/show/6024803-downbelow-station">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/81146844-amanda?shelf=2020-tbr-challenge">2020-tbr-challenge</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/81146844-amanda?shelf=owned">owned</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2956682034" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15653739918600942549">This was a hard one for me to rate. The plot was definitely intriguing and I loved following the twists and connection, but the sheer <i>number</i> of characters and quick cuts between scenes sometimes left me struggling to keep up. Still, the skillful construction of the storyline, the warmth of many of the characters, and moments that came out of nowhere to punch me in the feels, were enough to bring this to 4 stars.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


